      • ban

        public void ban(CommandExecutor banner,
       String reason,
       boolean kick,
       boolean banip)
        Ban this player.
        This method will execute a BanRequest Event. If this server does not have a ban plugin, then the player wont be banned.
        If the kick parameter is true, then the player will be kicked from the server with the message "Banned: reason" where reason is specified in the reason parameter.
        Parameters:
        banner - The client who is doing the banning.
        reason - The reason for banning this player.
        kick - Whether this player should be kicked as well.
        banip - Whether to ban the player's IP as well.

      • setRawPrefix

        public void setRawPrefix(String prefix)
        Set something to go before the user's username. This can be a title or a star. This prefix wont appear above the players head, unless isShowingPrefix() is true. The prefix will appear before the player's username in chat regardless of the value that is returned in isShowingPrefix(). Setting the player's prefix using this method will set the raw prefix. If the player has a title color it will be overwritten. Also, this method won't include the title brackets unless they're included in the prefix parameter. To cleanly set a prefix use the method setCleanPrefix(java.lang.String). The prefix assigned will also be saved as a extradata value with the key "mcf_prefix"
        Parameters:
        prefix - The prefix to set. You should include title brackets here.

      • setCleanPrefix

        public void setCleanPrefix(String prefix)
        Sets the player's prefix to the specified prefix. This method won't overwrite the player's title color and it will show the player's title brackets. To set the player's raw prefix use setRawPrefix(String)
        Parameters:
        prefix - - The prefix to set. Title brackets shouldn't be included here.

        public static void setAttribute(String key,
                Object object,
                String username,
                Server server)
                         throws SQLException,
                                IOException,
                                NotSerializableException

        Parameters:
        key - The name of the value
        object - The value
        username - The username to save

        Throws:

        IOException - If there was a problem writing the object to the SQL getServer().

        public void saveAttribute(String key)
        Save the value "key" to the database. The object "key" represents will be serialized to the database. No exceptions will be raised, if you need to know if an exception was caught, then please use saveAttributeRaised(String)
        Parameters:
        key -

      • globalBlockChange

        public void globalBlockChange(BlockUpdate[] blockupdates)
        Cause this player to place a series of blocks in the current level this player is in. You can get the current level by calling getLevel(). This method will execute a PlayerBlockChangeEvent event for each BlockUpdate object in the array passed in the parameter. If an event is canceled, then that block update will be skipped.
        Parameters:
        blockupdates - An array of BlockUpdate objects that contain the data for each block change.
